<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="236" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,690,1293]" pageId="35" pageNumber="236">
Diagnosis. Glp-1 not found. Ds-2 on membranous cuticle. PE with 1 dorsal seta. GA bipartite in female and male. Female with 6 Pgs. Male with 20 Pgs and 6 Sgs. Tr I–IV with 1-0-1-1 setae; Bf I–IV with 2-2-1-1 setae; Tf I–IV with 4-3-3-3 setae, 2-1-0-0 Bp setae; Gn I–IV with 4-4-2-3 setae, 2-1-0-0 Bp setae; Tb I–IV with 8-7-7-7 setae, 5-4-4-4 Bp setae; Ta I–IV with 3-3-3-3 dorsal setae, without Bp setae. Lc I with unidentate accessory process. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ausserer" authorityYear="1871" box="[151,255,871,897]" class="Arachnida" family="Idiopidae" genus="Idiosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="35" pageNumber="240" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Idiosoma</taxonomicName>
length 
<quantity box="[340,468,870,897]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0414" metricValueMax="1.143" metricValueMin="0.9398" pageId="35" pageNumber="236" unit="in" value="410.0" valueMax="450.0" valueMin="370.0">370–450 in</quantity>
adult. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ausserer" authorityYear="1871" box="[545,649,871,897]" class="Arachnida" family="Idiopidae" genus="Idiosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="35" pageNumber="240" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Idiosoma</taxonomicName>
