0.67–0.79. Ratio of P-2 to P-1 2.63.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,690,1293]" pageId="35" pageNumber="236">
Remarks. This species is distinguished from congeners by the shape of 
<collectingRegion box="[1016,1059,979,1005]" country="Serbia" name="Ada" pageId="35" pageNumber="236">AD</collectingRegion>
, the lack of Glps on dorsum, and the absence of Bp setae on Ta I–IV. Female and male are known.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,690,1293]" box="[208,1420,1051,1077]" pageId="35" pageNumber="236">
Habitat. Sublittoral zone: Sandy sediment, sediment with algae, and coarse or shell gravels at 
<quantity box="[1258,1343,1051,1077]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="0.6" pageId="35" pageNumber="236" unit="m" value="12.0" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="6.0">6–18 m</quantity>
depth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,690,1293]" pageId="35" pageNumber="236">
Distribution. North Atlantic Ocean: Roscoff (Bay of Morlaix), Le Croisic (Bay of Biscay) [
<collectingCountry box="[1218,1303,1086,1113]" name="France" pageId="35" pageNumber="236">France</collectingCountry>
]. West 
<collectingRegion box="[1380,1436,1087,1113]" country="Ireland" name="Cork" pageId="35" pageNumber="236">Cork</collectingRegion>
[
<collectingCountry box="[158,246,1122,1149]" name="Ireland" pageId="35" pageNumber="236">Ireland</collectingCountry>
]. 
<collectingRegion box="[263,375,1123,1149]" country="United Kingdom" name="Plymouth" pageId="35" pageNumber="236">Plymouth</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[386,454,1123,1149]" country="United Kingdom" name="Down" pageId="35" pageNumber="236">Down</collectingRegion>
[
<collectingCountry box="[469,517,1122,1149]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="35" pageNumber="236">UK</collectingCountry>
]. Mediterranean: Île Riou [
<collectingCountry box="[817,902,1122,1149]" name="France" pageId="35" pageNumber="236">France</collectingCountry>
].
</paragraph>
